1
00:00:00,094 --> 00:00:01,094
Yeah, right.

2
00:00:01,119 --> 00:00:03,006
I'm so boring. So bland, right?

3
00:00:03,031 --> 00:00:05,560
That's why last night
you fell asleep on me!

4
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:06,824
- Right?
- Oh!

5
00:00:06,849 --> 00:00:08,920
We had to adjust a bit.

6
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:10,040
It's not a common thing.

7
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:13,101
But as long as
the three of us are happy,

8
00:00:13,126 --> 00:00:14,480
I think it's possible.

9
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:16,280
Since we love each other...

10
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:20,335
but there's a problem
in the bedroom.

11
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,132
If you can find an outlet...

12
00:00:22,156 --> 00:00:24,637
then we won't have to
get mad at each other.

13
00:00:24,662 --> 00:00:28,600
Are you sure
that you really want to try this?

14
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:31,950
You choose now, between me...

15
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:33,840
and this old man.

16
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:53,440
"I can't sleep."

17
00:01:28,557 --> 00:01:30,455
- "Ouch."
- "Ikkyu the Psycho Sissy."

18
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,640
"Don't play with him."

19
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:34,120
"Kick him out of the group chat."

20
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,588
"Stay away from him."

21
00:01:35,613 --> 00:01:37,240
- "Ban Ikkyu."
- "Ban Ikkyu."

22
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:45,205
- "Ban Ikkyu!"
- "Ban Ikkyu!"

23
00:01:50,806 --> 00:01:53,775
"And now Mom is making me
sleep at Uncle Ohn's tomorrow."

24
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,980
"I really don't want to go."

25
00:02:08,104 --> 00:02:10,120
Welcome to my castle!

26
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:14,160
Glad to have Ikkyu in
Uncle Ohn and Uncle Jee's Castle!

27
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:17,320
Castle? More like a hassle.

28
00:02:17,858 --> 00:02:20,640
Hey, why did you say that, sweetie?

29
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,840
No, no, no, no, no.

30
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,680
You're just my uncle.
I am your nephew.

31
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,356
Mama Aom is my real mother.

32
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,400
What's wrong now?

33
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,160
You usually get along with him.

34
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:37,528
Today you have to stay here and
you're stomping like an elephant.

35
00:02:37,553 --> 00:02:39,815
Mom, I'm not an elephant.

36
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,383
Why would I be stomping?

37
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,000
I just want to go home.

38
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,680
We talked about this.

39
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,455
I have a seminar
upcountry for several days.

40
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:52,455
Since school's out,
if I leave you alone with Grandma,

41
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,960
you'll give her
a headache for sure.

42
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,200
Just stay with Uncle Ohn.

43
00:02:58,482 --> 00:03:02,400
Oh right, you've never
been apart from Mom.

44
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,440
But I guarantee,

45
00:03:05,925 --> 00:03:07,757
staying here with me,

46
00:03:07,782 --> 00:03:11,982
you'll have a blast.
You won't even want to go home.

47
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,640
Don't exaggerate.
I just want some peace and quiet.

48
00:03:16,203 --> 00:03:17,203
What?

49
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:22,175
I'm counting on you, Ohn.
It takes one to know one.

50
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:26,646
An old witch like you can
handle a little witch like Ikkyu.

51
00:03:26,671 --> 00:03:27,751
- Sis!
- Mom!

52
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:31,000
What witch is this cute?

53
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:34,851
Right?
How dare she call us witches?

54
00:03:34,876 --> 00:03:36,538
- Hmm.
- Mmm.

55
00:03:39,025 --> 00:03:42,043
He's no trouble at all.
Easy to take care of.

56
00:03:42,068 --> 00:03:44,400
Just no soggy food.

57
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:47,703
- Fried eggs or omelets are fine.
- Hmm.

58
00:03:47,703 --> 00:03:50,080
Don't worry, Ohn. I'm off now.

59
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:52,238
- Mom...
- Bye bye, sweetie.

60
00:03:53,387 --> 00:03:54,960
Bye bye...

61
00:04:06,692 --> 00:04:08,065
Is this your desk?

62
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,800
Mmm-hmm.

63
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:16,160
Oh. Kittima,
Sorceress of the Enchanted City.

64
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,063
Such an ancient cartoon.

65
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,155
Did you write this?

66
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:27,588
Yes. I wrote and drew it myself.

67
00:04:27,613 --> 00:04:28,680
Isn't it beautiful?

68
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,080
If it was considered
beautiful back then, then sure.

69
00:04:31,566 --> 00:04:34,400
Ouch! It's not that old.

70
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,855
What is the story about?

71
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,613
I think you'd told me before,
but I can't remember now.

72
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,640
This story...

73
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:48,280
I based it on a friend of mine.

74
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,003
About 40 years ago,

75
00:04:52,842 --> 00:04:55,280
there was a boy named Kit.

76
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:01,603
He was born male, but deep down,

77
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,240
he felt like a woman inside.

78
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,016
Just like you, Ikkyu.

79
00:05:09,636 --> 00:05:11,842
Hey Ud, you look like a movie star.

80
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:13,640
Never strike out with the ladies.

81
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,160
What nonsense is this?

82
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,655
A guy like me is way hotter
than a movie star.

83
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,680
Puh-lease!

84
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:23,560
Gosh, seeing that makes
me constipated already.

85
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,040
What's going on?

86
00:05:26,746 --> 00:05:28,936
Hey Kit, what are you doing?

87
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,160
Wait, are you a sissy?

88
00:05:31,938 --> 00:05:33,429
So you like men?

89
00:05:33,454 --> 00:05:36,680
Eww. Pervert. It's unnatural.

90
00:05:37,149 --> 00:05:38,337
Gives me the creeps.

91
00:05:38,362 --> 00:05:39,362
Brr...

92
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:45,040
Stay back! You make my skin crawl.

93
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,200
Okay, I'm leaving.

94
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:49,840
Wait a minute.

95
00:05:51,406 --> 00:05:54,200
We've got a freak in our school.
I can't just let him walk away.

96
00:05:57,074 --> 00:05:59,095
You don't like
being a proper man, huh?

97
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,040
You don't need that anymore, right?

98
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,120
Fine.

99
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,503
I'll do you a favor
and burn it off for you.

100
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:12,500
"Inappropriate behavior.
Do not imitate."

101
00:06:12,525 --> 00:06:14,471
- Grab him!
- Hey! Where are you going?

102
00:06:14,496 --> 00:06:17,354
"Inappropriate behavior.
Do not imitate."

103
00:06:17,379 --> 00:06:18,640
Did you piss yourself?

104
00:06:18,665 --> 00:06:20,000
- Shut up!
- Hold still!

105
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:22,365
Let me go!

106
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,040
- Hold him!
- Let go of me!

107
00:06:24,064 --> 00:06:25,320
- Take his pants off!
- Quiet!

108
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:26,944
"Inappropriate behavior.
Do not imitate."

109
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:28,796
Hurry up! Can't you stay still?

110
00:06:29,238 --> 00:06:30,480
Hold him down!

111
00:06:31,336 --> 00:06:32,366
Bring it here.

112
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:33,486
You're not using it, right?

113
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,400
- I'll get rid of it for you.
- Don't!

114
00:06:37,885 --> 00:06:40,480
"Inappropriate behavior.
Do not imitate."

115
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,072
Kit was assaulted by his peers.

116
00:06:43,446 --> 00:06:44,623
Mocked and bullied.

117
00:06:47,799 --> 00:06:49,490
The teachers weren't much help.

118
00:06:50,495 --> 00:06:52,143
His parents were ashamed.

119
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,590
They thought he was possessed.

120
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,040
His father, mother, teachers,...

121
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,651
"Boys don't wear things like this."

122
00:07:03,676 --> 00:07:04,851
"Take it off."

123
00:07:04,876 --> 00:07:07,676
and everyone
at school despised him.

124
00:07:08,103 --> 00:07:10,000
He had nowhere to turn.

125
00:07:27,225 --> 00:07:30,585
Eventually, he found a way
to escape from this world

126
00:07:32,024 --> 00:07:33,603
where he has never been happy.

127
00:07:39,556 --> 00:07:42,110
He found the gate
to the Enchanted City.

128
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,716
A place where
she could be anything.

129
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,855
So Kit became
the beautiful Sorceress Kittima.

130
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:52,616
Using her magic
to save villagers from Witch Laila.

131
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:57,381
Fighting alongside Reef,
the mighty warrior,

132
00:07:57,406 --> 00:08:00,288
and Duckman, his trusty sidekick.

133
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,360
Kittima found her happy place.

134
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,529
A place where she was valued.

135
00:08:04,554 --> 00:08:07,375
So she decided to stay
in the Enchanted City

136
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,170
and never came back.

137
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:19,143
So, is Uncle Kit dead?

138
00:08:19,614 --> 00:08:20,614
Hmm?

139
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:22,940
Hold on...

140
00:08:24,338 --> 00:08:25,440
Who died?

141
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,920
She justs became a Sorceress
living in the Enchanted City!

142
00:08:30,172 --> 00:08:33,455
Oh please, Uncle Ohn,
that's just a cartoon.

143
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,000
In real life, Uncle Kit...

144
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,816
Never mind.
You probably don't want to say.

145
00:08:42,482 --> 00:08:46,219
How many decades ago
was Uncle Kit's story?

146
00:08:46,244 --> 00:08:49,216
You said the world has changed,
and accepts people like us now.

147
00:08:49,893 --> 00:08:51,760
So why am I still getting bullied?

148
00:08:51,785 --> 00:08:53,150
Ikkyu.

149
00:08:54,172 --> 00:08:56,400
You have to accept the truth.

150
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:59,022
No matter what era it is,

151
00:08:59,047 --> 00:09:02,016
there'll always be people who
understand, and those who don't.

152
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,895
Trust me. Just do as I say.

153
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:08,895
If someone teases you, don't worry.

154
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,040
Just fight back.

155
00:09:11,972 --> 00:09:12,972
Trust you?

156
00:09:13,819 --> 00:09:15,840
Because I trusted you...

157
00:09:16,679 --> 00:09:18,880
Wait, what happened?

158
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,040
Hey!

159
00:09:38,626 --> 00:09:40,906
What the heck is that dance?
You look ridiculous.

160
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:45,480
It's Nokko.
You don't know? You're so basic.

161
00:09:45,809 --> 00:09:48,898
Are you a sissy? That's gross.

162
00:09:48,923 --> 00:09:51,206
Ikkyu the Sissy! Sissy Ikkyu!

163
00:09:51,231 --> 00:09:57,093
- Ikkyu is a sissy!
- Ikkyu is a sissy!

164
00:09:57,093 --> 00:09:58,336
Don't say that!

165
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,116
Why can't I say it?

166
00:10:00,928 --> 00:10:02,120
It's the truth, isn't it?

167
00:10:03,956 --> 00:10:07,058
"Remember, Ikkyu.
If anyone bullies you,"

168
00:10:07,698 --> 00:10:08,880
"just punch them."

169
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,780
"Better not punch them."

170
00:10:11,805 --> 00:10:15,249
"We shouldn't use
violence to solve problems."

171
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:18,960
"Let's just say
insulting them is enough."

172
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,040
I'll just insult them.

173
00:10:24,223 --> 00:10:25,606
You're so narrow-minded!

174
00:10:25,631 --> 00:10:28,834
Don't you know the world
is full of fabulous people now?

175
00:10:29,811 --> 00:10:31,480
I just want to be myself.

176
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,297
Why is that your problem?

177
00:10:33,321 --> 00:10:34,900
You dinosaurs!

178
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,760
Get him!

179
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
What are you doing?

180
00:10:40,351 --> 00:10:41,351
Ouch!

181
00:10:43,304 --> 00:10:44,304
Stop!

182
00:10:45,117 --> 00:10:46,117
Ouch!

183
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,500
Ikkyu the Psycho Sissy.

184
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:50,946
Let's not play with him.

185
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,118
Kick him out of the group.

186
00:10:53,143 --> 00:10:54,421
Don't talk to him.

187
00:10:54,446 --> 00:10:55,453
Ban Ikkyu.

188
00:10:55,478 --> 00:11:01,498
- Ban Ikkyu!
- Ban Ikkyu!

189
00:11:01,522 --> 00:11:05,345
- Ban Ikkyu!
- Ban Ikkyu!

190
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:07,080
Hey, stop that!

191
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,920
Teacher, Ikkyu punched me.

192
00:11:21,906 --> 00:11:23,106
"Get him!"

193
00:11:23,456 --> 00:11:25,870
"What are you doing? Stop!"

194
00:11:26,499 --> 00:11:27,499
"Ouch!"

195
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,278
"Ikkyu the Psycho Sissy.
Let's not play with him."

196
00:11:31,303 --> 00:11:33,934
"Kick him out of the chat.
Don't talk to him."

197
00:11:33,959 --> 00:11:36,718
- "Ban Ikkyu!"
- "Ban Ikkyu!"

198
00:11:36,743 --> 00:11:37,785
"Ikkyu, dangerous."

199
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:38,845
"Troublemaker."

200
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:39,872
"Violent freak!"

201
00:11:39,897 --> 00:11:41,961
"Stay away."

202
00:11:51,204 --> 00:11:54,200
I insulted them and fought back
just like you taught me.

203
00:11:54,699 --> 00:11:55,800
And what did I get?

204
00:11:56,238 --> 00:11:57,520
Punished by the teacher.

205
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,240
And my friends won't talk to me.

206
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,240
I see...

207
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:06,120
So that's why.

208
00:12:07,002 --> 00:12:08,440
You're mad at me.

209
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:13,735
I don't know
what you'll teach me next.

210
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,360
How much can I even trust it?

211
00:12:16,186 --> 00:12:18,426
You're old now.

212
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,692
Everything you teach is outdated.

213
00:12:21,351 --> 00:12:24,309
Times have changed.
Don't you know that?

214
00:12:24,334 --> 00:12:25,354
Hey now.

215
00:12:26,166 --> 00:12:28,086
But you said it yourself.

216
00:12:28,563 --> 00:12:31,240
It's been years
since Uncle Kit's time,

217
00:12:31,264 --> 00:12:32,799
yet you're still getting bullied.

218
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:35,885
Exactly.

219
00:12:35,909 --> 00:12:38,306
Even Uncle Kit couldn't handle it.

220
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:40,040
As for me...

221
00:12:49,586 --> 00:12:50,586
Ikkyu.

222
00:12:52,165 --> 00:12:55,000
If following my advice
got you into trouble,

223
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,613
then I am truly sorry.

224
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,880
But you have to
be stronger than Kit.

225
00:13:05,226 --> 00:13:06,366
You have to endure it.

226
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:10,440
If my advice didn't work,

227
00:13:10,832 --> 00:13:13,392
try finding a solution yourself.

228
00:13:18,020 --> 00:13:19,440
There's nothing I can do.

229
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:24,520
I'm banned. No one plays with me.

230
00:13:25,473 --> 00:13:28,218
I'll be hanging out
alone from 7th grade

231
00:13:28,243 --> 00:13:30,080
to 8th grade, 9th grade,

232
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,313
10th grade, 11th grade,

233
00:13:32,731 --> 00:13:34,053
and even 12th grade.

234
00:13:34,583 --> 00:13:37,400
I'll be lonely
and become a troubled kid.

235
00:13:38,091 --> 00:13:39,280
Oh please.

236
00:13:40,278 --> 00:13:41,680
So dramatic.

237
00:13:42,703 --> 00:13:44,286
Kids forget things easily.

238
00:13:45,127 --> 00:13:46,708
They'll forget
once the semester starts.

239
00:13:48,332 --> 00:13:51,301
Actually, I think this is good.

240
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,559
Let nature filter your friends.

241
00:13:55,403 --> 00:13:59,405
Just ignore the bad ones.

242
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,560
Choose friends with some maturity.

243
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,400
Look...

244
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:08,880
You're growing up
to be a teenager now.

245
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:29,480
- Put it down.
- Okay.

246
00:14:29,949 --> 00:14:32,160
One, two, three... Up!

247
00:14:39,637 --> 00:14:43,450
Gosh, everyone!
There's one stray baby sissy.

248
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:01,847
"Sorceress Kittima,
no one reads that anymore."

249
00:15:01,872 --> 00:15:06,840
"We need something
fresh, new, and totally viral."

250
00:15:08,675 --> 00:15:10,920
"Please find a new door for us."

251
00:15:16,532 --> 00:15:19,680
She won't let me write a sequel.

252
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:24,520
And I can't think of a new story.

253
00:15:44,395 --> 00:15:45,395
Hmm...

254
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:47,544
Oh, you're back, Jee?

255
00:15:47,569 --> 00:15:48,569
Yeah.

256
00:15:49,397 --> 00:15:51,153
All these for Ikkyu?

257
00:15:51,178 --> 00:15:52,178
Here.

258
00:15:52,203 --> 00:15:53,906
Come on. I'll set the table.

259
00:15:53,931 --> 00:15:54,937
Okay.

260
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,600
Whoa.

261
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,760
Pizza too? Ikkyu's gonna love this.

262
00:16:02,811 --> 00:16:05,458
So many things! Woohoo!

263
00:16:05,483 --> 00:16:06,760
I'm home!

264
00:16:06,785 --> 00:16:08,940
Oh, you're back, Ikkyu?

265
00:16:10,686 --> 00:16:11,720
Hello, Uncle Jee.

266
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,760
Hello there. Just in time.
Come have pizza with us.

267
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:15,880
Got a feast here.

268
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:18,680
- Whoa, pizza!
- Mmm.

269
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:19,880
My favorite!

270
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:22,175
Thank you so much, Uncle Jee!

271
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,600
So, where did you go, Ikkyu?

272
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:28,960
Just a walk in the park.
I met some friends too.

273
00:16:28,985 --> 00:16:30,772
Hmm? Friends?

274
00:16:30,796 --> 00:16:32,796
Kids from the neighborhood?

275
00:16:33,358 --> 00:16:34,358
Yes.

276
00:16:51,554 --> 00:16:53,208
Hello, Miss.

277
00:16:53,232 --> 00:16:55,056
Nice wig.

278
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:58,160
How rude! This is my real hair.

279
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:01,040
Sorry. My bad.

280
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:02,720
Your hair is gorgeous.

281
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,775
Come on, Kyoho. Don't mind the kid.

282
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,880
I'm Geon.

283
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,640
Chic name. Is it foreign?

284
00:17:13,016 --> 00:17:14,266
It's English.

285
00:17:14,891 --> 00:17:16,240
Geon as in Pigeon.

286
00:17:17,016 --> 00:17:19,640
During the pregnancy, his mom
craved Pigeon Brand Pickles.

287
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,120
I see.

288
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,520
And I'm Lemon, Geon's boyfriend.

289
00:17:26,593 --> 00:17:28,455
And Miss Bob Hair here...

290
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,760
is Kyoho.

291
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:32,867
I'm Ikkyu.

292
00:17:32,891 --> 00:17:34,891
Staying with my uncle
for the break.

293
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,520
Nice to meet you all.

294
00:17:38,709 --> 00:17:42,520
Hmm. If you get bored,
come hang out with us.

295
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,600
So you won't be lonely. Okay?

296
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Okay.

297
00:18:00,966 --> 00:18:02,752
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

298
00:18:04,606 --> 00:18:07,863
I really wish they had
Grilled Pork Neck Pizza.

299
00:18:07,888 --> 00:18:08,968
Zesty!

300
00:18:09,797 --> 00:18:10,830
Flaming hot?

301
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,080
Hey, Ikkyu.

302
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,440
Can I ask for your advice?

303
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:24,000
A kid like me?
What advice can I give?

304
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,720
Why does age matter?

305
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:27,887
I think...

306
00:18:28,286 --> 00:18:32,360
everyone has a perspective
that can be useful to others.

307
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:36,493
I want advice on my cartoon.

308
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:40,240
I'm asking you as a reader.

309
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,680
With pleasure.

310
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:48,020
About Kittima,
Sorceress of the Enchanted City.

311
00:18:48,984 --> 00:18:52,960
How do you think
I should continue the story?

312
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,560
Eww.

313
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:57,925
Hey, listen first! You brat.

314
00:18:57,950 --> 00:18:58,950
Sheesh.

315
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:01,400
I know that...

316
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:07,300
for this generation,
the story isn't fun anymore.

317
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:11,800
But if I take

318
00:19:12,441 --> 00:19:15,240
the parts that still work
and build on them,

319
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:19,040
how do you think
I should write the next chapter?

320
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:02,240
Oh, Ikkyu.

321
00:20:03,873 --> 00:20:05,920
What's wrong? Can't sleep?

322
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,560
I'm scared to sleep alone.

323
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,480
Can I sleep here?

324
00:20:12,087 --> 00:20:13,680
Come on. Sleep with us.

325
00:20:16,196 --> 00:20:17,880
Come squeeze in the middle.

326
00:20:20,337 --> 00:20:21,370
Come on.

327
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,880
Hmm!

328
00:20:42,381 --> 00:20:45,530
Can I sleep here, Uncle Jee?
I'm scared of ghosts.

329
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:48,880
Hmm.

330
00:20:50,360 --> 00:20:51,360
Okay.

331
00:21:19,148 --> 00:21:20,496
Mmm.

332
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,680
Smells delicious.

333
00:21:22,499 --> 00:21:23,605
- Jee?
- Hmm?

334
00:21:23,630 --> 00:21:25,280
- Want some more?
- Nnh.

335
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:27,720
Got to go.

336
00:21:29,309 --> 00:21:31,195
- Got to go now.
- Leaving already?

337
00:21:31,670 --> 00:21:33,618
- Mwah.
- Mwah.

338
00:21:35,545 --> 00:21:36,545
Oops.

339
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:38,068
Have a good day, Uncle Jee.

340
00:21:38,068 --> 00:21:41,221
Okay, thanks. See you later. Bye.

341
00:21:41,246 --> 00:21:42,683
Have a seat, Ikkyu.

342
00:21:42,724 --> 00:21:43,730
Okay.

343
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:47,280
Mmm...

344
00:21:48,357 --> 00:21:49,600
Here.

345
00:21:57,503 --> 00:22:00,160
Here's breakfast.

346
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,880
It's my Signature Shrimp Congee.

347
00:22:06,670 --> 00:22:07,670
Okay.

348
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,640
Have a taste.

349
00:22:31,329 --> 00:22:32,680
How is it?

350
00:22:40,551 --> 00:22:43,440
Hey, Ik... Ikkyu! What's wrong?

351
00:22:45,379 --> 00:22:47,280
Wait, maybe...

352
00:22:48,356 --> 00:22:50,120
Is he allergic to shrimp?

353
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:54,360
No way. Aom didn't say anything.

354
00:22:56,484 --> 00:22:59,320
He's no trouble at all.
Easy to take care of.

355
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:02,520
Just no soggy food.

356
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,960
Fried eggs or omelets are fine.

357
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:07,000
Don't worry, Ohn.

358
00:23:07,745 --> 00:23:09,080
Oh...

359
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:11,200
I forgot!

360
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:16,920
Aom said Ikkyu hates soggy food.

361
00:23:21,499 --> 00:23:25,240
Hello, Aom.
Why is he such a picky eater?

362
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:29,636
If I told you he was picky,
you wouldn't take him!

363
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:31,120
Oh, Aom!

364
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,200
How am I supposed to
take care of him?

365
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,903
He won't eat anything I cook.

366
00:23:35,370 --> 00:23:37,720
I had to order fried chicken!

367
00:23:38,425 --> 00:23:40,437
Just ask him what he wants.

368
00:23:40,462 --> 00:23:42,665
It's not hard.
You'll get used to it.

369
00:23:42,690 --> 00:23:45,969
When you cook rice,
make sure it's dry.

370
00:23:45,994 --> 00:23:50,367
Crispy over-hard fried eggs.

371
00:23:50,799 --> 00:23:53,132
Omelets shouldn't be too oily.

372
00:23:53,157 --> 00:23:54,220
That's all.

373
00:23:54,777 --> 00:23:57,760
Hey, they're calling me. Gotta go!

374
00:23:57,785 --> 00:23:58,920
Okay, okay.

375
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,160
How is it? Delicious?

376
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,960
Next time when I'm not in a rush,

377
00:24:11,985 --> 00:24:15,800
I'll cook something you like.

378
00:24:16,493 --> 00:24:17,567
Okay.

379
00:24:17,592 --> 00:24:20,520
Today, you're coming
to work with me.

380
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:24,440
Okay. I promise I'll behave.

381
00:24:24,852 --> 00:24:26,972
Good. Eat up.

382
00:24:45,312 --> 00:24:46,352
Nidnoi.

383
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:48,840
Nidnoi.

384
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:55,040
You're awake?

385
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:56,040
Mmm.

386
00:24:56,356 --> 00:24:57,356
Does it hurt?

387
00:24:57,946 --> 00:24:58,946
Nidnoi.

388
00:25:00,699 --> 00:25:02,760
Why do you keep calling my name?

389
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:07,440
Because you make everything better.

390
00:25:08,166 --> 00:25:10,446
Being sweet? You must be okay then.

391
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:14,230
I'm not trying to be sweet.
It really helps.

392
00:25:15,849 --> 00:25:16,849
But...

393
00:25:17,670 --> 00:25:19,670
it feels good to get it out.

394
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:22,119
Are you thirsty?

395
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:23,920
Nidnoi.

396
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:28,000
Want some water?

397
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,040
Nidnoi.

398
00:25:40,990 --> 00:25:42,480
Hey, Ikkyu.

399
00:25:43,286 --> 00:25:46,727
Hang out here for a bit.
Don't wander off anywhere.

400
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:50,387
I have a meeting.
I'll come back in a bit. Okay?

401
00:25:50,412 --> 00:25:52,612
Go do your work, Uncle Ohn.
Don't worry about me.

402
00:25:52,637 --> 00:25:54,600
Okay. See you in a bit then.

403
00:25:54,624 --> 00:25:55,898
- Mmm.
- Give me a hug.

404
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:58,120
- Mmm...
- Mmm...

405
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:01,200
I'll be back. Be good.

406
00:26:22,184 --> 00:26:23,184
Sky.

407
00:26:23,911 --> 00:26:27,280
Wait for me here.
Just a quick meeting. I'll be fast.

408
00:26:27,305 --> 00:26:28,305
Yes, Dad.

409
00:26:30,427 --> 00:26:31,427
Go on.

410
00:26:34,036 --> 00:26:35,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

411
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:36,493
Play with your friend, son.

412
00:26:36,981 --> 00:26:38,080
Okay.

413
00:26:42,050 --> 00:26:43,070
Hmm...

414
00:26:44,075 --> 00:26:45,760
Dad or Mom?

415
00:26:46,652 --> 00:26:47,760
I am confused.

416
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,560
- Hello, Ohn.
- Hello, everyone.

417
00:27:02,584 --> 00:27:03,646
- Hello.
- Hello.

418
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:11,880
Hello everyone.

419
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,200
- Hello.
- Hello, Kong.

420
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:15,136
Sorry I'm a bit late.

421
00:27:15,161 --> 00:27:17,680
Sky tagged along today.

422
00:27:18,144 --> 00:27:20,240
I left him in the Relaxing Zone.

423
00:27:22,293 --> 00:27:26,341
"Uh oh. Kong's son,
alone with Ikkyu?"

424
00:27:26,366 --> 00:27:28,140
"Will they fight?"

425
00:27:29,030 --> 00:27:30,080
Ready for today?

426
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,480
So ready.

427
00:27:48,862 --> 00:27:50,040
Sky, right?

428
00:27:50,561 --> 00:27:52,560
I heard your Dom call you.

429
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:54,240
Mad.

430
00:27:54,365 --> 00:27:55,520
Mom, wait.

431
00:27:55,998 --> 00:27:57,120
Dad, wait.

432
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,520
Dad was correct.

433
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,280
I'm Ikkyu. Wanna dance?

434
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,000
No thanks. I can't dance.

435
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,000
Mmm.

436
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:24,880
Don't stare at me. I'm shy.

437
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:29,120
I'm not good at dancing either.
I just like doing it.

438
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,760
Why don't you play with your phone?

439
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,560
I can't. My dad taught me...

440
00:28:36,834 --> 00:28:39,327
when you're with someone,
don't play on your phone.

441
00:28:39,352 --> 00:28:40,680
Pay attention to them.

442
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:45,520
Whoa. So proper. Such a gentleman.

443
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:49,000
I never thought about that before.

444
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,360
Cute.

445
00:28:56,746 --> 00:28:57,840
But not good enough.

446
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:59,520
What?

447
00:29:00,493 --> 00:29:01,508
Why not?

448
00:29:01,533 --> 00:29:05,360
I told you. We need to
go beyond Kittima now.

449
00:29:06,215 --> 00:29:08,600
Whoa, this is going beyond.

450
00:29:09,508 --> 00:29:12,914
Go beyond the 2D comic Kittima,

451
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:16,360
into a new format, stickers.

452
00:29:16,385 --> 00:29:18,358
We sell them
on the app and website.

453
00:29:18,383 --> 00:29:20,120
Zero extra investment.

454
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:23,000
Think of it as company merchandise.

455
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:26,116
To attract customers or
bring back old Kittima fans.

456
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,240
Ohn, don't you have any new ideas?

457
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,000
I do.

458
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,040
Of course I do.

459
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:35,627
My ideas never run out.

460
00:29:36,391 --> 00:29:39,006
I just wanted to
pitch the sticker idea first.

461
00:29:39,006 --> 00:29:41,440
In case anyone was interested.

462
00:29:42,163 --> 00:29:46,080
I'm looking forward to hearing
some good news from you, Ohn.

463
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:49,000
So...

464
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,600
We're listening, Ohn.

465
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,360
Thank you for the question.

466
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:07,920
Regarding Kittima,
Sorceress of the Enchanted City.

467
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:12,606
I think the story teaches people
to run away from their problems.

468
00:30:12,631 --> 00:30:13,766
- Hmm?
- Hmm?

469
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:16,880
But there are
some interesting points.

470
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:20,640
What are the rules
of the Enchanted City?

471
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:26,880
Well, like Kit wanted
to be a girl, so she became one.

472
00:30:28,331 --> 00:30:30,760
And what about
the Duckman guy? Who is he?

473
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,400
Why did he want a duck's head?

474
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,720
Is he dead like Uncle Kit?

475
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:39,640
Uh well, Duckman...

476
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:42,320
He represents people who...

477
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,560
are unremarkable. Just like a duck.

478
00:30:45,115 --> 00:30:48,400
Jack of all trades, master of none.

479
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:52,720
And the handsome guy
with long hair? The archer?

480
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:56,880
That's Reef. He is a brave warrior.

481
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,837
A muscular, manly warrior.

482
00:31:01,368 --> 00:31:03,120
But he's weaker than Kittima?

483
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,640
Hold on. Are you saying

484
00:31:05,664 --> 00:31:08,614
my story doesn't make any sense?

485
00:31:09,715 --> 00:31:10,995
I don't know, Uncle Ohn.

486
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:15,600
Famous cartoons
don't always make sense either.

487
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,560
But they're fun.

488
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:21,640
You read them to
see what crazy idea comes next.

489
00:31:22,133 --> 00:31:23,133
Hmm.

490
00:31:23,158 --> 00:31:27,320
Your story is full of crazy ideas,
but it's interesting.

491
00:31:29,080 --> 00:31:31,560
If you want to
tell a story, just tell it.

492
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:34,840
- Don't get stuck on Kittima.
- Hmm.

493
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:37,160
She's probably reincarnated by now.

494
00:31:38,838 --> 00:31:39,838
Oh...

495
00:31:41,699 --> 00:31:43,699
If you want to use me

496
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:47,640
as a character in your story,
I totally don't mind.

497
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,080
Oh, you little...

498
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:57,120
Thank you for the answer.
It was very useful.

499
00:31:57,150 --> 00:31:58,317
- Excellent.
- You're welcome.

500
00:32:03,363 --> 00:32:06,200
I'm going to create a spinoff.

501
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:10,080
Focusing on the other characters
in the Enchanted City.

502
00:32:10,873 --> 00:32:13,599
The ones we
didn't explore in the first part.

503
00:32:15,951 --> 00:32:18,040
Will Kittima appear again?

504
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,080
Oh, no.

505
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:22,240
It's the universe
of Duckman and Reef.

506
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,600
And the other wild creatures.

507
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:30,120
It will tell the backstory
of Duckman and Reef.

508
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:35,320
Living amidst the wonders
of the Enchanted City,

509
00:32:35,675 --> 00:32:39,603
while Duckman has no
special skills at all.

510
00:32:39,628 --> 00:32:41,855
But he has to survive,

511
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,840
and help his best friend, Reef,

512
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:48,240
who seems to be good at everything.

513
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:50,710
Everyone pins their hopes on Reef.

514
00:32:51,483 --> 00:32:54,680
But actually, Reef is useless.

515
00:32:55,311 --> 00:32:58,364
Can't shoot straight.
All talk, no action.

516
00:32:58,389 --> 00:33:01,754
He goes around
promising to help everyone,

517
00:33:01,779 --> 00:33:04,007
trying to solve
everyone's problems.

518
00:33:04,350 --> 00:33:05,560
Wait, Ohn.

519
00:33:06,961 --> 00:33:08,850
You're making a story

520
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:14,520
about the adventures of
losers in a wonderland?

521
00:33:15,320 --> 00:33:16,480
Exactly.

522
00:33:16,723 --> 00:33:19,866
And we'll add
an LGBTQ kid character

523
00:33:19,890 --> 00:33:21,416
from the present day,

524
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,200
who falls into the Enchanted City,

525
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:26,375
living with them and
helping them solve problems,

526
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:28,800
using the Gen Alpha mindset.

527
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:32,040
This is completely different, Ohn.

528
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,680
It's a totally new direction.

529
00:33:39,015 --> 00:33:41,360
But I'm starting to like it.

530
00:33:50,353 --> 00:33:54,840
Sky, if you don't like dancing,
what do you like?

531
00:33:55,660 --> 00:33:56,940
I like cooking.

532
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,320
That's unusual.

533
00:34:00,169 --> 00:34:02,160
Sometimes I want to
eat stuff I see on TikTok.

534
00:34:02,989 --> 00:34:04,640
But I don't want to
ask Dad to buy it.

535
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,520
So I learned to make it myself.

536
00:34:07,633 --> 00:34:10,823
I even want to join
a junior chef cooking competition.

537
