802
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:56,000
It actually doesn't matter
how Chon presents herself.

803
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:58,000
Boobs or no boobs.

804
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:04,080
Because I love Chon
for her kindness...

805
00:49:04,869 --> 00:49:06,640
and always being by my side.

806
00:49:07,514 --> 00:49:09,560
Thank you.

807
00:49:09,585 --> 00:49:10,916
Mmm...

808
00:49:10,941 --> 00:49:12,880
Love you! Kiss, kiss, kiss.

809
00:49:12,880 --> 00:49:13,906
Love you too.

810
00:49:15,641 --> 00:49:16,641
Love you.

811
00:49:20,361 --> 00:49:22,200
Eww, stinks!

812
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:24,440
Love stinks!

813
00:49:25,327 --> 00:49:26,360
Whatever.

814
00:49:31,124 --> 00:49:32,280
After rinsing the rice,

815
00:49:32,585 --> 00:49:34,080
add just this much water.

816
00:49:34,680 --> 00:49:36,280
So it won't be too dry or too wet.

817
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,120
Remember that.

818
00:49:38,400 --> 00:49:39,400
Okay.

819
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:41,160
Like this.

820
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:53,880
When the pan is hot,
pour the egg in.

821
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:05,400
When the bottom
is golden brown, flip it.

822
00:50:10,753 --> 00:50:11,753
Smell good?

823
00:50:12,058 --> 00:50:13,058
Smells great!

824
00:50:16,451 --> 00:50:17,451
Mmm.

825
00:50:18,599 --> 00:50:19,599
Wow!

826
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:25,120
The chili paste is delicious, Jee!

827
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:26,600
So fragrant.

828
00:50:26,907 --> 00:50:28,120
This place is amazing.

829
00:50:28,487 --> 00:50:29,493
Mmm.

830
00:50:29,823 --> 00:50:30,833
Mmm.

831
00:50:32,262 --> 00:50:33,262
Ikkyu,

832
00:50:34,770 --> 00:50:37,015
won't you eat anything else?

833
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:39,600
Uncle Kong bought
so much other food.

834
00:50:40,265 --> 00:50:42,840
Why only eat the omelet you made?

835
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:47,120
I want to taste
my own cooking first.

836
00:50:47,402 --> 00:50:48,960
It feels so good.

837
00:50:48,985 --> 00:50:50,200
- Mmm!
- Mmm!

838
00:50:50,225 --> 00:50:53,760
Let me taste it.
Let's see how good it is.

839
00:50:54,694 --> 00:50:55,714
Go ahead.

840
00:50:57,097 --> 00:50:58,878
You're really good these days.

841
00:50:59,378 --> 00:51:01,544
Now you can even teach
your friend how to cook.

842
00:51:01,880 --> 00:51:05,080
Ikkyu learns fast.
He's easy to teach.

843
00:51:05,291 --> 00:51:07,880
Good job.

844
00:51:10,440 --> 00:51:11,486
Mmm!

845
00:51:11,557 --> 00:51:12,590
How is it?

846
00:51:12,760 --> 00:51:14,400
The omelet's so crispy.

847
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:15,440
- Mmm!
- Mmm!

848
00:51:15,464 --> 00:51:16,904
- Well done, kiddo.
- Very talented.

849
00:51:20,974 --> 00:51:21,974
There.

850
00:51:22,427 --> 00:51:23,960
Pull the blanket.

851
00:51:23,985 --> 00:51:25,960
Uncle Kong was good with kids.

852
00:51:25,984 --> 00:51:27,984
Sky's a good kid.
I'm happy for him.

853
00:51:28,880 --> 00:51:29,953
- Really?
- Mmm.

854
00:51:30,759 --> 00:51:33,200
Jee, have you ever wanted kids?

855
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,200
Like, doing GIFT or something?

856
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:39,680
Never.

857
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:43,840
I can't picture myself
raising a child.

858
00:51:45,640 --> 00:51:47,454
- Why not, Uncle Jee?
- Hmm?

859
00:51:47,751 --> 00:51:52,080
- I'd love to. I love kids.
- Hmm.

860
00:51:52,080 --> 00:51:55,360
Someday, I want to have a baby.
I want to be a mother.

861
00:51:55,643 --> 00:51:57,680
- Wow...
- Hmm...

862
00:51:57,939 --> 00:51:59,560
What an imagination.

863
00:52:01,031 --> 00:52:02,144
Ikkyu,

864
00:52:02,168 --> 00:52:05,297
raising a child is very hard.

865
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:09,160
I didn't say it was easy.

866
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:12,960
But for you two,
it would be a breeze.

867
00:52:13,140 --> 00:52:14,733
You're both great with kids.

868
00:52:16,394 --> 00:52:18,720
You sure are a sweet talker.

869
00:52:19,159 --> 00:52:20,511
- Smooth.
- Smooth.

870
00:52:22,560 --> 00:52:26,320
Can I cuddle with
the sweet talker tonight then?

871
00:52:26,498 --> 00:52:27,498
Mmm.

872
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:29,280
Lights out, Uncle Jee.

873
00:52:29,525 --> 00:52:31,560
Okay.

874
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:36,320
Come here.

875
00:52:36,923 --> 00:52:37,923
Mwah!

876
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:39,606
Mmm...

877
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:43,880
Mmm-hmm.

878
00:52:50,228 --> 00:52:52,480
Mmm...

879
00:52:53,603 --> 00:52:56,000
Come visit again soon, okay?

880
00:52:56,722 --> 00:52:57,722
Yes.

881
00:52:58,240 --> 00:52:59,560
Let's go home, dear.

882
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:02,440
- I don't want to go back yet, Mom.
- What?

883
00:53:02,465 --> 00:53:03,960
I want to stay with my Uncles.

884
00:53:04,525 --> 00:53:05,560
Hmm...

885
00:53:05,585 --> 00:53:07,520
Please, Mom, please.

886
00:53:07,960 --> 00:53:09,451
You're so dramatic.

887
00:53:09,476 --> 00:53:12,255
You didn't want to come,
now you don't want to leave.

888
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:15,160
What a baby. Let's go home.

889
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:17,200
You can come back another day.

890
00:53:17,811 --> 00:53:18,811
Okay.

891
00:53:19,571 --> 00:53:21,000
- Bye bye, Uncle Ohn.
- Bye bye.

892
00:53:21,930 --> 00:53:23,160
- See you later.
- See you.

893
00:53:23,519 --> 00:53:24,912
- Get in the car. Go on.
- Here.

894
00:53:24,937 --> 00:53:25,937
Thank you.

895
00:53:29,504 --> 00:53:30,583
- Aom.
- Hmm?

896
00:53:30,965 --> 00:53:32,440
Keep an eye on Ikkyu.

897
00:53:33,400 --> 00:53:34,963
He's hanging out
with kids around here,

898
00:53:34,987 --> 00:53:37,055
trying to take birth control pills.

899
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:39,560
What? Is he growing up that fast?

900
00:53:40,034 --> 00:53:42,081
- Apparently.
- Oh boy...

901
00:53:42,105 --> 00:53:44,665
- Take him to see a doctor.
- Hmm.

902
00:53:44,690 --> 00:53:47,073
Don't let him take pills
by himself. It's dangerous.

903
00:53:47,998 --> 00:53:49,520
- Thanks, Ohn.
- Hmm.

904
00:53:51,217 --> 00:53:52,217
Go on.

905
00:53:52,381 --> 00:53:53,960
- Sawasdee krub.
- Sawasdee ka.

906
00:53:54,380 --> 00:53:56,517
- Come on, dear.
- Drive safe, Aom.

907
00:53:56,541 --> 00:53:57,601
Okay.

908
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,680
- Jee.
- Hmm?

909
00:54:15,889 --> 00:54:18,680
When I tried on Ikkyu's wig,

910
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:22,200
it felt very strange.

911
00:54:23,920 --> 00:54:24,920
Strange how?

912
00:54:25,693 --> 00:54:29,283
Usually, I never felt like
I wanted to be a woman.

913
00:54:29,308 --> 00:54:30,308
Hmm.

914
00:54:30,480 --> 00:54:32,360
But when I put the wig on,

915
00:54:33,080 --> 00:54:34,498
I just felt that...

916
00:54:35,739 --> 00:54:37,040
I wanted...

917
00:54:38,310 --> 00:54:40,428
- a snatched waist.
- Hmm?

918
00:54:40,428 --> 00:54:42,840
To match the wig, I guess.

919
00:54:43,398 --> 00:54:44,438
Hmm.

920
00:54:44,954 --> 00:54:47,120
What's wrong with me?

921
00:54:48,160 --> 00:54:51,680
Why am I still
confused at this age?

922
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:53,680
It's no big deal.

923
00:54:54,978 --> 00:54:56,735
- It is, Jee.
- Hmm.

924
00:54:56,864 --> 00:55:00,688
If, one day, I decided to
dress as a woman for real,

925
00:55:00,713 --> 00:55:01,880
would you accept it?

926
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:03,640
Of course I would.

927
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:05,960
Whatever you are, I'm okay with it.

928
00:55:06,738 --> 00:55:11,240
Even if you get boobs and
long hair, I won't leave you.

929
00:55:12,589 --> 00:55:13,960
I might even join you.

930
00:55:15,201 --> 00:55:17,840
Did you know sometimes
I want to dress up too?

931
00:55:18,440 --> 00:55:19,440
Jee!

932
00:55:20,318 --> 00:55:21,600
You crazy old man.

933
00:55:22,115 --> 00:55:23,320
Tiny little waist.

934
00:55:24,657 --> 00:55:26,800
Jee! Stop it!

935
00:55:31,504 --> 00:55:34,120
Boiled peanuts. Boiled corn.

936
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:36,920
Boiled peanuts. Boiled corn.

937
00:56:02,623 --> 00:56:04,320
Teacher Boon has cancer.

938
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:09,360
I think my life right now is okay.

939
00:56:09,711 --> 00:56:11,659
If it's really okay like you say,

940
00:56:11,684 --> 00:56:12,913
then that's good.

941
00:56:13,261 --> 00:56:15,720
We are ready to
help you with everything.

942
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:19,800
I want to speak up
to protect myself

943
00:56:21,560 --> 00:56:23,640
and all other victims.

944
00:56:24,662 --> 00:56:26,040
I want everyone...

945
00:56:26,960 --> 00:56:28,880
to have the courage to stand up.

946
00:56:29,343 --> 00:56:30,903
That's a lie!

947
00:56:31,547 --> 00:56:33,320
That's not true!

948
00:56:33,345 --> 00:56:37,960
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

949
00:56:37,960 --> 00:56:41,528
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

950
00:56:41,552 --> 00:56:44,073
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
